originalText.text:
This is Stop number 5 in my continuing journey to try every bagel place in Manhattan.

We arrived at 9:45 AM and there was about 10 people in front of us. Over the next five minutes there was a line 30 people long dragging out into the street.  The cashier was very polite fast to take out order and answered our questions.  It was $50 for 2 bagels and an OJ + coke. Pretty nuts.  But upon opening the bag, it is obvious that they are huge. They are probably the biggest sized bagels I have gotten so far. And believe it or not the price for the bagel is average to slightly below what other establishments cost for a Lox bagel.  ðŸ¥¯

Overall, I would give the place a seven out of 10. It was absolutely nothing wrong with the bagel. It just wasnâ€™t as good as some places and it was a little bit limited on the amount of salmon that was given. A perfectly average place to grab a bagel.

originalText.text:
Spoiled for choice! There are many combination of bagels to choose from. You may choose different bagels with different fillings which leads to either a sweet or savoury bagel, or even a mixture of both if youâ€™re so inclined.

My personal recommendation is to go heavy on the cream cheese as it makes the bagel easier to consume since it can be a bit dry. On top of the cream cheese (any flavour), you may add other ingredients as you wish.

I would also highly recommend to dine out as there are limited seats for dining in. The place is also not cleaned as often as it should be, leaving the mess from previous patrons for the next.

The staff at the counter was very friendly and would recommend the bagels based on what your personal taste is. For the more health conscious, there are different wraps available.
